SIMPLE: incitement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incitement
<hw>In*cite"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>incitement</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of inciting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which incites the mind, or moves to action;
motive; incentive; impulse.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From the long records of a distant age,⟦br⟧
Derive <qex>incitements</qex> to renew thy rage.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Motive; incentive; spur; stimulus; impulse;
encouragement.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inciter</ent>⟦br⟧
